The paper proposes a method for estimating the accuracy of classifiers, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The approach is based on logical constraints, which are often used in natural language processing and knowledge representation (cs.CL). The method is also probabilistic in nature, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on real-world datasets, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) or cybersecurity (cs.CR) applications.
